decisions.description:
The main goal of this flow is to create an Event ( a type of Activity ). But we must create that Event within an existing record.
If all previous attempts at finding a record failed ( via SFID, or Invitee Email ): then we need to create a record.
We will always create a Lead Staging record, when we couldn't find a record.
decisions.name: Do_we_have_a_Record
decisions.label: Do we have a Record?

decisions.description:
While looking up the records, if we found one, we would have set the OwnerId as the record owner.
In the last step, we attempted to overwrite the OwnerId with the id of the user whose email matches the publisher.
So at this point, we hope to have an owner defined. If we don't we'll have to look up the system admin.

textTemplates.name: rtEmailBodyUnidentifiedEvent
textTemplates.text:
Dear IT,


A Calendly Booking has been made for an event type, that is currently not being handled.

Link to record


See below information for reference:

Event name: {!$Record.Calendly__EventTypeName__c}

Slug: {!$Record.Calendly__EventTypeSlug__c}

Kind: {!$Record}{!$Record.Calendly__EventTypeKind__c}

Record ID: {!$Record.Id}

User Email: {!$Record.Calendly__EventPrimaryPublisherName__c}

User Name: {!$Record.Calendly__EventPrimaryPublisherName__c}


Proposed Cause of Action

  1. Identify the Event in question
  2. Figure out where the link is available to customers, if you don't already know
  3. Determine whether or not a Campaign Member needs to be created for the event type
